      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Avignon Wine Tour"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Daniel and I have recently become fairly interested in wine, so we were curious to learn more about the industry while traveling Europe. We had read great reviews about Avignon Wine Tour, a company run by a local named Francois. Francois offers a tour of a different region each day of the week. We picked the Saturday tour of the famous Châteauneuf du Pape, a French wine "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "em"
              }
            ],
            "text": "appellation d'origine contrôlée"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " (AOC) - a highly respected certification given to specific areas in France for wine as well as other things like cheese, butter, and meats."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The AOC sets many different standards for the wine and how it's produced. Much like similar regulations in other countries, the AOC also has rules surrounding the wine label and how to read it. Using the card in the picture below, we learned how to read a label to determine which level of AOC quality the wine is. You won't find the type of grape varietal printed on the label like you would on a bottle in the United States, but rather the region from which the wine was produced."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "image",
            "attrs": {
              "src": "images/20160206_095002-e1478778900125-1024x674.jpg",
              "alt": "20160206_095002",
              "title": null
            },
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "http://www.everydayaccountsblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/20160206_095002-e1478778900125.jpg",
                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Most wine produced in the Châteauneuf du Pape is red, and much of the red wine is made of the grenache and syrah grapes."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "We visited three local wineries and had lunch in the area. Despite the winter season and dried up vines, it was beautiful countryside to explore and learn about from a very knowledgable local. Francois knew an incredible amount about the wine and the area. We hope to go back one day and do another tour!"
          }
        ]
